1
00:00:14,767 --> 00:00:15,733
Amanda?

2
00:00:15,800 --> 00:00:18,400
Was it you who had
this hat reserved?

3
00:00:18,467 --> 00:00:19,600
Why didn't you buy it?

4
00:00:19,667 --> 00:00:20,733
Are you short on money?

5
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,967
Don't keep it all to yourself.

6
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:27,233
You might get drunk and get in
trouble with Yenyen again.

7
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:30,567
I don't know if my mom is the
one threatening Aunt Rina.

8
00:00:30,633 --> 00:00:32,533
You talk as if your mom
has turned into a terrorist.

9
00:00:32,600 --> 00:00:33,700
She loves you so much.

10
00:00:33,800 --> 00:00:39,867
A lot of love could turn
into a lot of hate.

11
00:00:39,933 --> 00:00:40,900
So you hate her too?

12
00:00:40,967 --> 00:00:43,000
Is it wrong to hate my mother?

13
00:00:43,067 --> 00:00:45,633
Amanda can't be Mrs. Madrigal!

14
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,367
I thought I saw a ghost.

15
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:48,633
It is a ghost.

16
00:00:48,700 --> 00:00:49,633
A snake remains a snake

17
00:00:49,700 --> 00:00:54,700
no matter how often
it sheds its skin.

18
00:00:54,767 --> 00:00:57,567
At least they turn
more beautiful

19
00:00:57,633 --> 00:00:59,033
after they shed their skin.

20
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,800
Unlike some people.

21
00:01:00,867 --> 00:01:05,200
The store manager said you seem
to have some financial problems.

22
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:12,500
Have you moved on without Eden?

23
00:01:12,567 --> 00:01:15,933
To make you smile,
let's take a picture.

24
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:17,233
Cheese!

25
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:17,933
Nothing.

26
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,167
What is it?

27
00:01:19,233 --> 00:01:20,600
- Turn around.
- Turn around.

28
00:01:20,667 --> 00:01:21,267
Reverse.

29
00:01:21,667 --> 00:01:22,333
Reverse.

30
00:01:23,067 --> 00:01:24,167
- I'm getting dizzy.
- Turn around once more.

31
00:01:25,900 --> 00:01:26,800
Oh my God!

32
00:01:29,733 --> 00:01:39,700
Red!

33
00:01:44,700 --> 00:01:50,700
Red!

34
00:01:50,767 --> 00:01:56,833
All I know is that Amanda
wants to forget her past.

35
00:01:59,467 --> 00:02:01,433
Amanda's happy
with her life now.

36
00:02:03,767 --> 00:02:05,167
She holds no grudge
in her heart.

37
00:02:05,933 --> 00:02:06,733
Are you sure?

38
00:02:10,100 --> 00:02:11,533
Are you afraid of my wife?

39
00:02:15,267 --> 00:02:19,300
I don't know how
it can affect our deal.

40
00:02:20,833 --> 00:02:21,567
Affect our deal?

41
00:02:23,100 --> 00:02:24,333
Didn't I make it clear?

42
00:02:25,200 --> 00:02:28,933
Amanda had put her
past behind her.

43
00:02:29,967 --> 00:02:30,800
So...

44
00:02:31,867 --> 00:02:34,667
nothing can change our deal,
Victor.

45
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:39,667
Unless, you want to back out.

46
00:02:41,067 --> 00:02:43,633
Can you give back the money
I loaned you?

47
00:02:45,167 --> 00:02:46,300
Do you still have the money?

48
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:49,167
What money?

49
00:02:52,267 --> 00:02:53,767
Mrs. Ramos, you're here.

50
00:02:57,033 --> 00:03:00,500
Rina, please meet
Lucho Madrigal.

51
00:03:00,567 --> 00:03:02,367
Lucho, my wife, Rina.

52
00:03:02,433 --> 00:03:04,300
So what money are you
two talking about?

53
00:03:05,833 --> 00:03:07,900
We're just talking about...

54
00:03:08,967 --> 00:03:11,333
your husband's investment
in our business.

55
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,500
I don't want him to pass on
the opportunity to make money.

56
00:03:16,733 --> 00:03:19,667
So think about it.

57
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:25,233
Because it will be your loss
if you back out.

58
00:03:29,167 --> 00:03:29,767
Excuse me.

59
00:03:55,467 --> 00:03:55,867
Yen!

60
00:03:57,367 --> 00:03:57,833
Yen!

61
00:03:58,667 --> 00:04:01,867
Yen, please, wait.

62
00:04:01,933 --> 00:04:03,100
It's not what you think.

63
00:04:04,633 --> 00:04:06,400
Sab and I were just
being friendly.

64
00:04:06,467 --> 00:04:09,633
She probably felt that I
was sad because...

65
00:04:09,700 --> 00:04:10,533
Because of me?

66
00:04:13,633 --> 00:04:14,667
When we started
our relationship,

67
00:04:14,733 --> 00:04:17,500
my greatest joy was
to make you smile.

68
00:04:17,567 --> 00:04:20,067
Even if we're going
through hard times.

69
00:04:21,467 --> 00:04:22,867
That's why it's so painful...

70
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:27,433
to see someone else
make you smile.

71
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,467
I can't make you smile...

72
00:04:33,967 --> 00:04:36,167
because of what happened
to our baby.

73
00:04:37,867 --> 00:04:39,367
I'm still confused, Red.

74
00:04:40,600 --> 00:04:43,500
I'm still sad.
I feel like I'm all alone.

75
00:04:45,167 --> 00:04:46,933
So I'm sorry.

76
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,200
I'm sorry that I can't
make you smile anymore.

77
00:04:49,267 --> 00:04:51,133
I'm sorry if you're not happy
with me anymore.

78
00:04:54,967 --> 00:04:56,800
Perhaps your mom is right.

79
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:02,033
Maybe we should rethink
our relationship.

80
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:05,333
What?

81
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:12,400
Are you still going through

82
00:05:12,467 --> 00:05:15,167
with your business deal
with Lucho Madrigal?

83
00:05:15,233 --> 00:05:17,233
Now that we know that
his wife is Amanda?

84
00:05:18,133 --> 00:05:20,500
Can we just talk about
this at home, Rina?

85
00:05:20,567 --> 00:05:22,567
My head hurts with everything
that's happening.

86
00:05:22,633 --> 00:05:23,300
Fine!

87
00:05:24,667 --> 00:05:27,200
Because I just want
to leave this place.

88
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,500
So this is why they
have a huge house...

89
00:05:32,200 --> 00:05:34,933
and throw a lavish party

90
00:05:35,033 --> 00:05:39,767
because they're hiding
a big bag of stinky garbage!

91
00:05:39,833 --> 00:05:40,600
And that's Amanda!

92
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,300
Stop it, Rina.
Someone might hear you.

93
00:05:44,133 --> 00:05:48,033
House blessing, my foot.

94
00:05:48,100 --> 00:05:49,233
She can't fool me!

95
00:05:49,833 --> 00:05:51,900
She can't outsmart me.

96
00:05:53,567 --> 00:05:56,467
I still have an ace against her.

97
00:05:57,633 --> 00:05:58,200
Rina...

98
00:05:59,867 --> 00:06:00,267
What?

99
00:06:06,367 --> 00:06:08,033
Auntie, Uncle.

100
00:06:08,133 --> 00:06:08,833
Yes, Sab?

101
00:06:11,200 --> 00:06:12,467
Sab, where's Red?

102
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:15,400
Can you find him and tell him
we're leaving now?

103
00:06:17,200 --> 00:06:19,600
He's out in the garden
trying to get to Yenyen.

104
00:06:19,667 --> 00:06:21,300
Eden's here?

105
00:06:21,367 --> 00:06:22,733
Yes.

106
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,733
Let's go.

107
00:06:27,200 --> 00:06:28,567
What is she doing here?

108
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:36,300
Are you saying we should
break up again?

109
00:06:39,433 --> 00:06:40,633
This is so tiring.

110
00:06:41,167 --> 00:06:42,400
We've had this talk before.

111
00:06:43,467 --> 00:06:46,800
You always want to break up
over little things!

112
00:06:48,467 --> 00:06:49,700
We've been through
a lot already.

113
00:06:49,767 --> 00:06:51,700
We've overcome a lot
of problems together.

114
00:06:53,067 --> 00:06:55,867
And you'll let me go in a snap?

115
00:06:57,833 --> 00:06:59,800
What do we have left
to fight for?

116
00:06:59,867 --> 00:07:03,367
Our baby's gone and
all we do now is fight.

117
00:07:05,967 --> 00:07:07,067
That's what I'm saying.

118
00:07:07,133 --> 00:07:09,267
Red and I are having
such a great time.

119
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:13,367
Yenyen showed up all of a
sudden.

120
00:07:14,500 --> 00:07:16,833
She gatecrashed this party
just to fight with Red.

121
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:17,967
Can you believe?

122
00:07:19,333 --> 00:07:22,433
Oh my God,
that girl is so annoying!

123
00:07:23,233 --> 00:07:23,900
Yes!

124
00:07:26,467 --> 00:07:26,900
Red!

125
00:07:28,467 --> 00:07:29,467
Red! Eden!

126
00:07:30,467 --> 00:07:31,867
What are you two doing?

127
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:35,467
Why are you fighting here?
Aren't you ashamed?

128
00:07:35,533 --> 00:07:37,333
Someone might see you.

129
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:38,700
I'm sorry, Auntie.

130
00:07:38,767 --> 00:07:41,633
Eden, this is not okay!

131
00:07:41,700 --> 00:07:43,833
What are you doing here?

132
00:07:43,900 --> 00:07:48,067
It has only been a week
since that happened to you.

133
00:07:49,700 --> 00:07:54,233
You might have a relapse.
This is not good for you.

134
00:07:55,267 --> 00:07:56,467
I'm really sorry.

135
00:07:57,633 --> 00:08:00,900
Let's just go home.

136
00:08:00,967 --> 00:08:01,667
Let's go home.

137
00:08:01,733 --> 00:08:03,533
Mom, I'll take her home.

138
00:08:04,233 --> 00:08:05,133
You should go back inside.

139
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,933
Mr. Madrigal might
be looking for you.

140
00:08:09,400 --> 00:08:11,667
Amanda, are you
looking for someone?

141
00:08:12,867 --> 00:08:14,100
Yes.

142
00:08:14,167 --> 00:08:16,733
You know the Ramoses, right?

143
00:08:16,800 --> 00:08:17,900
Do you know their son Red?

144
00:08:19,333 --> 00:08:22,067
It seems that Red is the most
wanted person tonight.

145
00:08:22,167 --> 00:08:24,833
His girlfriend was looking for
him earlier.

146
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:26,300
His girlfriend is here?

147
00:08:27,433 --> 00:08:30,533
- Actually, Red...
- No, no.

148
00:08:30,600 --> 00:08:31,400
You know what?

149
00:08:32,300 --> 00:08:34,900
They won't even notice
that we left.

150
00:08:34,967 --> 00:08:36,633
They have a lot of guests.

151
00:08:37,433 --> 00:08:39,467
Let's just go home.

152
00:08:39,533 --> 00:08:41,133
Eden is tired.

153
00:08:45,300 --> 00:08:47,467
She went outside
by the parking area.

154
00:08:47,933 --> 00:08:49,267
Okay, excuse me.

155
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:50,067
Amanda, are you okay?

156
00:08:50,133 --> 00:08:51,300
Yes. I am.

157
00:09:02,367 --> 00:09:03,067
Be careful.

158
00:09:03,133 --> 00:09:04,200
Watch your step.

159
00:09:31,200 --> 00:09:31,667
Eden.

160
00:09:40,733 --> 00:09:41,333
Eden?

161
00:10:06,533 --> 00:10:07,400
Wait.

162
00:10:09,333 --> 00:10:10,867
Congratulations!

163
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:12,600
Love...

164
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:16,567
your grand reveal
is very successful,

165
00:10:17,300 --> 00:10:20,267
especially with Rina and Victor.

166
00:10:22,100 --> 00:10:24,667
I almost laughed earlier.

167
00:10:26,400 --> 00:10:28,033
Especially when I saw Rina.

168
00:10:28,967 --> 00:10:30,133
Victor almost...

169
00:10:31,667 --> 00:10:35,467
confessed everything
they did to you.

170
00:10:37,767 --> 00:10:38,833
But don't worry.

171
00:10:40,733 --> 00:10:44,300
I made him believe
that you have moved on.

172
00:10:45,233 --> 00:10:47,767
He agreed to everything I said.

173
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:50,667
Otherwise, he'll have to give me
my money back.

174
00:10:54,367 --> 00:10:54,867
Love?

175
00:10:57,200 --> 00:10:57,967
Amanda?

176
00:11:00,767 --> 00:11:01,267
Sorry.

177
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,667
I was thinking about something.

178
00:11:06,500 --> 00:11:07,500
Is there a problem?

179
00:11:09,633 --> 00:11:12,700
Aren't we supposed
to be celebrating?

180
00:11:12,767 --> 00:11:15,567
Because our plan was a success.

181
00:11:15,633 --> 00:11:17,300
Your enemies were terrified.

182
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:21,233
Eden was here earlier.

183
00:11:22,633 --> 00:11:23,800
I think she's having
a problem with her

184
00:11:23,867 --> 00:11:24,633
relationship with Red.

185
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,733
I tried to find her.

186
00:11:30,400 --> 00:11:31,700
But I didn't let her see me.

187
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:35,400
I just wanted to see her.

188
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:39,367
I don't know if she's already
given birth or not yet.

189
00:11:39,667 --> 00:11:40,133
I wonder...

190
00:11:43,367 --> 00:11:45,733
if my grandchild
is a girl or a boy.

191
00:11:46,967 --> 00:11:48,300
But I didn't get to see her.

192
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:52,067
I just wanted to know
how she's doing.

193
00:11:52,133 --> 00:11:53,667
I can't get her out of my mind.

194
00:12:03,200 --> 00:12:04,100
But, Amanda...

195
00:12:06,000 --> 00:12:07,500
it's not the time yet, Amanda.

196
00:12:08,767 --> 00:12:09,800
We have a plan.

197
00:12:11,467 --> 00:12:12,800
You can't get distracted now.

198
00:12:15,867 --> 00:12:17,400
Victor is making sure...

199
00:12:19,067 --> 00:12:20,500
your daughter is
well taken care of.

200
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:25,167
They treat her...

201
00:12:26,867 --> 00:12:28,000
as their own.

202
00:12:30,800 --> 00:12:31,733
So...

203
00:12:33,133 --> 00:12:34,533
we have to stick
to our plan.

204
00:12:36,767 --> 00:12:42,767
Amanda, we have to
expose the Ramoses.

205
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:49,233
To make Eden realize that
she chose the wrong family.

206
00:12:51,167 --> 00:12:52,100
And after all of that...

207
00:12:54,433 --> 00:12:55,867
you can get your daughter back.

208
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,967
I'm sorry for ruining
your party.

209
00:13:20,633 --> 00:13:25,067
I don't know why I did that.
I'm not that kind of person.

210
00:13:26,067 --> 00:13:28,133
I wasn't thinking right.

211
00:13:29,500 --> 00:13:30,367
It's okay, Eden.

212
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:31,800
It's over now.

213
00:13:33,033 --> 00:13:35,367
Don't worry.
It won't happen again.

214
00:13:35,433 --> 00:13:36,333
I'm going back home.

215
00:13:37,433 --> 00:13:42,067
- What?
- What?

216
00:13:42,133 --> 00:13:43,567
I'm going back to my Aunt Dindi.

217
00:13:44,667 --> 00:13:47,767
Thank you for taking care of me
while I was pregnant.

218
00:13:48,933 --> 00:13:53,067
But now that my baby's gone,
I have no reason to stay here.

219
00:13:54,100 --> 00:13:56,600
And I don't see any future
with Red.

220
00:13:58,933 --> 00:14:00,000
There you go again, Yen.

221
00:14:01,233 --> 00:14:05,367
Deciding for both of us without
even talking to me.

222
00:14:05,433 --> 00:14:07,333
Look at how we talk
to each other.

223
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:10,033
We don't get along anymore.

224
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:14,400
Even your mom wants us
to separate.

225
00:14:14,467 --> 00:14:16,167
What? What are you
talking about?

226
00:14:17,333 --> 00:14:18,400
I never said that.

227
00:14:19,433 --> 00:14:21,700
I don't want the two of you
to break up.

228
00:14:23,133 --> 00:14:24,767
Eden, I'm sorry.

229
00:14:24,833 --> 00:14:27,633
I'm sorry if I made you
think that.

230
00:14:28,900 --> 00:14:33,000
I know that I've been harsh
to you and Red lately.

231
00:14:33,067 --> 00:14:34,667
Probably because
I've been stressed

232
00:14:34,733 --> 00:14:36,967
from those people
threatening me.

233
00:14:37,933 --> 00:14:40,767
But now that I know where those
threats are coming from,

234
00:14:41,567 --> 00:14:44,633
I think I can handle things
better now.

235
00:14:44,700 --> 00:14:46,333
Who's harassing you, Mom?

236
00:14:47,467 --> 00:14:50,300
That's not important right now.

237
00:14:50,367 --> 00:14:54,133
Your relationship with my son
is what matters right now.

238
00:14:55,067 --> 00:14:57,133
I don't want the two of you
to separate.

239
00:14:58,167 --> 00:14:59,567
Are you sure?

240
00:15:01,933 --> 00:15:02,633
Eden...

241
00:15:04,633 --> 00:15:07,367
I know you're going through
a hard time right now.

242
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:11,933
I know that you've gone
through things.

243
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,267
But you guys have overcome it,
right?

244
00:15:18,567 --> 00:15:19,333
Eden...

245
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:23,233
I don't want you to think,

246
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:27,467
that now the baby's gone...

247
00:15:28,700 --> 00:15:31,433
I don't care about you anymore,
no.

248
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,000
You're family.

249
00:15:37,833 --> 00:15:39,567
You're still a part
of the family.

250
00:15:40,767 --> 00:15:42,800
And that will never change.

251
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:56,833
Sab?

252
00:15:59,267 --> 00:16:00,767
I thought you were at the party
with Red.

253
00:16:01,967 --> 00:16:03,100
We were.

254
00:16:03,167 --> 00:16:06,733
We were having a good time,
and then Eden showed up.

255
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:08,033
Let me remind you.

256
00:16:08,933 --> 00:16:10,467
They are the ones
in a relationship.

257
00:16:11,467 --> 00:16:12,733
So if someone's
getting in the way...

258
00:16:14,233 --> 00:16:15,433
it's you.

259
00:16:15,500 --> 00:16:16,067
And...

260
00:16:17,467 --> 00:16:18,833
I thought you were over Red.

261
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:20,567
Fine!

262
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:22,900
But I'm not over him.

263
00:16:22,967 --> 00:16:25,300
I just said that so he wouldn't
feel awkward around me.

264
00:16:26,433 --> 00:16:29,567
So that we can remain friends,
and he will confide in me.

265
00:16:29,633 --> 00:16:30,367
Did it work?

266
00:16:31,533 --> 00:16:33,567
He's still coming home to Eden.

267
00:16:33,633 --> 00:16:35,433
That's why I'm done
playing nice.

268
00:16:35,500 --> 00:16:37,833
Now I know the weakness
of their relationship.

269
00:16:37,900 --> 00:16:40,100
And I can use that against them.

270
00:16:40,167 --> 00:16:42,400
And mark my words, Colby.

271
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,967
I will get Red back.

272
00:17:02,733 --> 00:17:03,633
What's going on, Rina?

273
00:17:04,467 --> 00:17:06,933
Why didn't you tell Eden
that her mom is back?

274
00:17:10,067 --> 00:17:12,333
She might hear you! Be quiet!

275
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:12,833
Why?

276
00:17:13,767 --> 00:17:14,533
What are you planning to do?

277
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:16,900
To be honest, for now,
I have nothing.

278
00:17:19,133 --> 00:17:21,200
Amanda caught me by surprise.

279
00:17:22,033 --> 00:17:23,133
But tomorrow...

280
00:17:24,467 --> 00:17:29,933
I'll be ready for anything
she has for me.

281
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:33,333
So please, Victor.

282
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:36,467
Don't say anything to Eden.

283
00:17:38,033 --> 00:17:43,000
I'm still planning on how I can
use her against her mom.

284
00:17:43,733 --> 00:17:44,667
So that's it.

285
00:17:46,100 --> 00:17:47,267
I was noticing you...

286
00:17:48,967 --> 00:17:51,633
how you tried to manipulate Red
to break up with Eden.

287
00:17:51,700 --> 00:17:55,633
But you've changed your mind
all of a sudden.

288
00:17:55,700 --> 00:17:58,367
Now, you want Eden
to stay here with us.

289
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:00,233
Of course.

290
00:18:01,600 --> 00:18:04,067
We can't let her leave.

291
00:18:06,300 --> 00:18:08,467
She's our ace against Amanda.

292
00:18:09,733 --> 00:18:10,233
Rina...

293
00:18:11,267 --> 00:18:12,967
why don't we just stop this?

294
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:17,300
Lucho told me,
that Amanda had left everything

295
00:18:17,367 --> 00:18:18,900
that had happened
to her in the past.

296
00:18:18,967 --> 00:18:21,000
And she just wants to move on.

297
00:18:21,067 --> 00:18:24,267
And honestly,
I also want us to move on.

298
00:18:26,267 --> 00:18:27,200
And you believe that?

299
00:18:28,933 --> 00:18:33,200
I do not trust that woman,
Victor.

300
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:40,200
I still have a feeling she's the
one who's been threatening me.

301
00:18:40,267 --> 00:18:41,467
You don't have proof!

302
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:45,733
Do I need proof?

303
00:18:47,400 --> 00:18:48,400
Please, Victor.

304
00:18:49,533 --> 00:18:51,267
We have to stay away
from the Madrigals.

305
00:18:51,333 --> 00:18:52,333
First thing in the morning...

306
00:18:53,767 --> 00:18:54,700
you need to back out

307
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:59,000
from your business deals
with Lucho Madrigal.

308
00:19:00,067 --> 00:19:01,467
Forget everything.

309
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:24,567
Sorry, Yen.

310
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,267
I should have done this
with you from the start.

311
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,400
I'm sorry I failed you.

312
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:42,633
I was only thinking
about my pain.

313
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,767
I didn't try to understand you.

314
00:19:49,967 --> 00:19:50,900
I didn't think about you.

315
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:03,600
We're both immature.

316
00:20:05,733 --> 00:20:07,667
We both don't know what to do.

317
00:20:12,667 --> 00:20:13,600
Honestly...

318
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:16,167
I still don't know what to do.

319
00:20:18,367 --> 00:20:22,433
I can't promise you
that I'm okay now.

320
00:20:24,667 --> 00:20:26,467
- Yes.
- That we're okay.

321
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:29,633
Yen, that's okay.

322
00:20:32,067 --> 00:20:33,633
We can still try.

323
00:20:38,467 --> 00:20:39,767
I still love you so much.

324
00:20:46,700 --> 00:20:48,533
I love you so much too.

325
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:02,867
I'm sorry.

326
00:21:05,400 --> 00:21:08,700
I'm glad that you two
have patched things up.

327
00:21:14,367 --> 00:21:14,967
Auntie...

328
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:18,600
Thank you for accepting me...

329
00:21:20,100 --> 00:21:21,533
even after the baby's gone.

330
00:21:22,367 --> 00:21:26,500
It wouldn't be fair to stop
caring about you,

331
00:21:27,467 --> 00:21:29,800
just because you lost the baby.

332
00:21:29,867 --> 00:21:32,367
It wasn't your fault, Eden.

333
00:21:33,500 --> 00:21:38,500
We all know that this
is all Amanda's fault.

334
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:43,433
That's why I think you should
put your baby to rest.

335
00:21:44,867 --> 00:21:48,667
Otherwise, you will
never find peace.

336
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:52,600
Because every time you see
your baby's urn,

337
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:57,400
you'll remember everything
your mom did to you.

338
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:01,900
We will bury your baby, Eden.

339
00:22:03,767 --> 00:22:05,467
And you should bury

340
00:22:05,533 --> 00:22:08,133
whatever love you have left
for your mother with it.

341
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:11,967
It's the only way for you
to find peace.

342
00:22:33,333 --> 00:22:34,133
Gosh!

343
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:37,800
This is so luxurious, Amanda.

344
00:22:38,667 --> 00:22:41,967
And I can't get over
your transformation.

345
00:22:43,267 --> 00:22:44,833
Do I get a makeover too?

346
00:22:49,133 --> 00:22:51,867
My dear sister!
I missed you, Dindi.

347
00:22:51,933 --> 00:22:53,333
- You're still funny.
- My gosh!

348
00:22:55,567 --> 00:22:56,300
I'm sorry...

349
00:22:57,400 --> 00:22:59,033
for not contacting you sooner.

350
00:22:59,100 --> 00:23:01,800
Me and Amanda had to sort out a
lot of things first.

351
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:04,167
Come on.

352
00:23:04,233 --> 00:23:06,300
Stop acting like a stranger.

353
00:23:06,367 --> 00:23:09,667
I know how crazy in love
you are with my sister.

354
00:23:09,733 --> 00:23:10,433
I'm just stating the truth.

355
00:23:12,567 --> 00:23:17,900
But honestly, Amanda.
I'm so happy for you.

356
00:23:17,967 --> 00:23:20,900
I was so worried about you
when you were gone.

357
00:23:20,967 --> 00:23:23,500
We've been looking
for you everywhere.

358
00:23:23,600 --> 00:23:27,100
And we keep praying
that you're okay.

359
00:23:28,333 --> 00:23:30,400
Turns out you're just busy
with your love life.

360
00:23:30,467 --> 00:23:33,133
I wish you'd sent me
some luck in love too.

361
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:34,733
Even a little will do!

362
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:36,500
I'm sorry.

363
00:23:39,067 --> 00:23:40,433
Is Eden here?

364
00:23:42,567 --> 00:23:43,600
Where is she, Amanda?

365
00:23:45,367 --> 00:23:46,200
We haven't...

366
00:23:49,700 --> 00:23:50,967
seen each other yet.

367
00:23:54,567 --> 00:23:55,833
Why not?

368
00:23:56,900 --> 00:23:59,600
Did you know what she's
going through right now?

369
00:23:59,667 --> 00:24:01,200
She's going through a lot.

370
00:24:02,767 --> 00:24:06,200
Her baby died right
after giving birth to her.

371
00:24:06,267 --> 00:24:06,633
What?

372
00:24:07,533 --> 00:24:08,100
The baby died?

373
00:24:09,567 --> 00:24:10,667
She said...

374
00:24:11,667 --> 00:24:13,867
they got into an accident on
their way to the hospital.

375
00:24:13,933 --> 00:24:15,600
And then she said they didn't
make it to the hospital,

376
00:24:15,667 --> 00:24:17,667
so they brought her
to a midwife.

377
00:24:18,600 --> 00:24:21,900
And the midwife told her

378
00:24:21,967 --> 00:24:27,133
that her baby suddenly
stopped breathing.

379
00:24:32,367 --> 00:24:36,400
Only one person can hurt
my daughter like this.

380
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:37,200
Only Rina can do this.

381
00:24:39,400 --> 00:24:42,300
Probably she has something to do
with the child's death.

382
00:24:48,500 --> 00:24:49,700
I miss you so much.

383
00:24:50,467 --> 00:24:51,500
I miss you too.

384
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:53,800
Wow!

385
00:24:53,867 --> 00:24:56,100
How sweet!

386
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:58,167
Sabina, what are you doing here?

387
00:24:58,233 --> 00:25:00,600
I'm here to invite you
to my birthday party.

388
00:25:00,667 --> 00:25:01,733
You're inviting me too?

389
00:25:01,800 --> 00:25:03,500
Of course!

390
00:25:03,600 --> 00:25:04,967
Red and I are friends.

391
00:25:05,033 --> 00:25:07,567
So maybe we can be friends too.

392
00:25:07,633 --> 00:25:09,367
She doesn't deserve him.

393
00:25:09,433 --> 00:25:11,800
She's making his life miserable.

394
00:25:11,867 --> 00:25:13,467
They just have to realize

395
00:25:13,533 --> 00:25:15,833
that they're not meant
for each other.

396
00:25:15,900 --> 00:25:17,833
And I think I can
help with that.

397
00:25:17,900 --> 00:25:20,700
We don't need to go if
you're not comfortable.

398
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:23,567
But is it okay if
I give her a gift?

399
00:25:23,633 --> 00:25:26,367
She's always being fuzzy.
Eden's full of drama.

400
00:25:26,433 --> 00:25:28,567
She's just like her mom.

401
00:25:28,633 --> 00:25:31,800
She's always causing
our family trouble.

402
00:25:31,867 --> 00:25:34,567
Good thing we got rid of the
baby.

403
00:25:34,633 --> 00:25:35,000
Mom?

404
00:25:37,733 --> 00:25:39,900
Are you talking about our baby?
